---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Treasure Mountain — Brott Studio"
  description="Treasure Mountain — Berry Dragon's Land. A tappable interactive map built for a single player: a small child with a big imagination."
>
  <header>
    <div class="hero-header">
      <img src="/icon.png" alt="Brott Studio" />
      <h1>Brott Studio</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-parent"><a href="/">← brott studio</a></div>
  </header>

  <section class="project-page">
    <h2>Treasure Mountain</h2>
    <p class="subtitle">Berry Dragon's Land</p>

    <p class="blurb">
      A tappable interactive map built for a single player: a small child with a big imagination.
    </p>

    <p class="blurb">
      The experience started as a hand-drawn map. We took that drawing, turned it into a living
      surface, and wired each region into its own little moment — Sunrise fades to dawn when you
      tap it, the Treeless Prairie has swaying grass blades, the Berry Dragon's lair breathes
      fire, and the House-Boat greets you with real ocean waves sampled from a beach track.
    </p>

    <p class="blurb">
      Every zone has its own ambience: gentle seagulls at the beach, deep bubbling at the
      Quicksand, soft chimes at Sunrise. Audio is strictly sandboxed per zone so nothing bleeds
      from one moment to the next.
    </p>

    <p class="blurb">
      Built to survive force-dark browsers, mobile taps, and enthusiastic retriggering by small
      fingers.
    </p>

    <div class="status">
      <strong>Shipped and delivered April 2026.</strong> Not publicly distributed — it belongs to one kid.
    </div>

    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="cta" href="https://brott-studio.github.io/treasure-mountain/">Visit the experience →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>A 100100 Productions venture. · <a href="/">brott-studio.github.io</a> · <a href="https://github.com/brott-studio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></p>
  </footer>
</Base>
